thread.title: Rex Ryan impressed by Bills fans traveling to Nashville for win over Titans

author: Matthew Fairburn | mfairburn@syracuse.com
title: Rex Ryan impressed by Bills fans traveling to Nashville for win over Titans
text:
Nashville, Tenn. — Buffalo took over Nashville for the Bills' Week 5 game against the Tennessee Titans.
It started Saturday, when Bills fans were spotted all over downtown Nashville, and it continued Sunday at Nissan Stadium, as those who traveled south got to see the Bills pull off a comeback, 14-13 victory . Bills coach Rex Ryan couldn't believe the turnout for such a long trip.
"You couldn't get into a restaurant yesterday without seeing Bills fans. It was awesome," Ryan said. "I guess something I'm learning, I had no idea that Bills fans travel the way they do. Miami was packed. Here it was unbelievable. That's such a great feeling to know that your guys are with you, your fans travel so well. I also love the fact that they aren't off this boat. They never looked to jump and we gave them some reason to, but they're sitting right there. That's a great feeling."
At one point during the game, an audible "Let's go Buffalo" chant broke out.
